
Overview of noun wafer

The noun wafer has 3 senses (first 1 from tagged texts)
                                          
1. (1) wafer -- (a small adhesive disk of paste; used to seal letters)
2. wafer -- (a small thin crisp cake or cookie)
3. wafer -- (thin disk of unleavened bread used in a religious service (especially in the celebration of the Eucharist))
